~~~ .php.xmp
Pager($input = [], $chunk = [5, 0], $path = true, $config = []); // @pages mode
Pager($input = [], $current = "", $path = true, $config = []); // @page mode
~~~

**Example:**

~~~ .php
$pager = new Pager([0, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7], [3, 0], 'foo/bar');
$pager_str = $pager . "";
~~~

Result:

~~~ .php
$pager = [
    'previous' => null,
    'hub' => 'foo/bar',
    'next' => 'foo/bar/2'
];
~~~

~~~ .php
$pager_str = '<span>◀</span> <a href="foo/bar">◆</a> <a href="foo/bar/2">▶</a>';
~~~

> **Info:** For item page pager, set the `$chunk` parameter to the array value you want treat as the current item.
>
> ~~~ .php
> $pager = new Pager(['-foo', '-bar', '-baz'], '-bar', 'foo/bar');
> ~~~
>
> Result:
>
> ~~~ .php
> $pager = [
>     'previous' => 'foo/bar/-foo',
>     'hub' => 'foo/bar',
>     'next' => 'foo/bar/-baz'
> ];
> ~~~